properties.headline: Winter Weather Advisory issued January 15 at 5:07AM EST until January 17 at 6:00AM EST by NWS Buffalo NY
properties.description:
* WHAT...Snow expected. Total snow accumulations of 3 to 6
inches. Winds gusting as high as 35 mph.

* WHERE...Wayne and Northern Cayuga counties.

* WHEN...From 7 AM Thursday to 6 AM EST Friday.

* IMPACTS...Plan on slippery road conditions. Areas of blowing
snow will significantly reduce visibility. The hazardous
conditions could impact the Thursday morning and or evening
commutes.
properties.instruction:
Periods of snow will result in snow covered roads and limited
visibilities. Slow down and use caution while driving.

Submit snow reports through our website or social media.

NWSheadline: WINTER WEATHER ADVISORY IN EFFECT FROM 7 AM THURSDAY TO 6 AM EST FRIDAY
